en Amtes.  aPope John XXII, elected in 1316, reigned for 18 years and was the most significant if also the most controversial of the Popes who resided in Avignon. The essays in this volume, drawn from the disciplines of history, art, philosophy, theology, and the law, examine the conceptual and institutional conditions and the impact of his papacy and seek to show the ways it was organized according to both time-honored and innovative practices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aChurch historyy14th centuryvCongresses. 4aKirchenrecht. 4aMittelalter. 4aPapsttum. 4aPolitische Geschichte. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aMiddle Ages.  aPapacy.  aecclesiastical law.  apolitical history.1 aBeattie, Blake, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBojcov, Michail A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrunner, Melanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuba, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGodthardt, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHitzbleck, Kerstin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJamme, Armand, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaufhold, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKerscher, Gottfried, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLambertini, Roberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMierau, Heike Johanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aModestin, Georg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb